Task 1



Brief Description

For this task, I created a digital literacy awareness infographic using Canva. 
The main idea behind my design was to explain digital literacy in a simple and visually engaging way so that students can easily understand its importance.


In my infographic, I included key sections such as “What is Digital Literacy,” “Useful Digital Tools for Students,” “Safe Internet Practices,” “Professional Online Presence,” and “Email Etiquette.” 
I used examples like Google Docs, GitHub, LinkedIn, and Canva to show how digital tools can be helpful for students in their academic work. 
I also highlighted important safety practices like using strong passwords, avoiding unknown links, and not sharing personal information.



While designing, I focused on keeping the layout clean and balanced, with proper use of colours, icons, and short points so that the content is easy to read.
One challenge I faced was organizing all the information without making the infographic look crowded.
This task helped me improve my creativity and taught me how to present information in a clear and effective way.


